# Step 1: Generate RSA private key
openssl genpkey -algorithm RSA -out server.key -aes256

# Step 2: Extract public key
openssl rsa -in server.key -pubout -out server.pub

# Step 3: Create a Certificate Signing Request (CSR)
openssl req -new -key server.key -out server.csr

# Step 4: Create a self-signed certificate (valid 365 days)
openssl req -x509 -key server.key -in server.csr -out server.crt -days 365

# Step 5: View certificate details
openssl x509 -in server.crt -text -noout


=========================================

📑 What you saw in output

    Modulus: Big hex block (your pasted part starting with d6:bf:90:6a...)

    Exponent: 65537 (standard RSA public exponent)

    Signature Algorithm: sha256WithRSAEncryption

    Signature Value: Hex block showing the actual certificate signature

👉 This confirms your certificate is valid and signed with RSA + SHA256.
